\par \pard\plain \s6\sa120 \f2\fs20\lang1033 Directives are used within {\uldb macros}{\v MacroLa}{\v nguage} to control what lines are executed and in what order.
\par \pard \s6\sa120 Directives always start with the exclamation mark "!" character and must be the first non-white text placed on a line. They are:
\par \pard\plain \s11\li360\tx2880 \f2\fs20\lang1033 {\uldb !BREAK}{\v .BREAK}
\par {\uldb !ENDM}{\v .ENDM}
\par {\uldb !FORCE}{\v .FORCE}
