\par \pard\plain \s6\sa120 \f2\fs20\lang1033 This {\uldb variable}{\v Variables} contains the current {\ul buffe}{\ul r}{\v Buffer}'s attribute flags, encoded as the sum of the following numbers:
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-1080\li1440\tx1440\tx2880 \f2\fs20\lang1033 1\tab Internal invisible buffer
\par 2\tab Changed since last read or write
\par 4\tab Buffer was truncated when read (due to lack of memory)
\par \pard \s7\fi-1080\li1440\sa120\tx1440\tx2880 8\tab Buffer has been {\uldb narrowed}{\v NarrowingYourScope}
\par \pard\plain \s6\sa120 \f2\fs20\lang1033 Only the invisible (1) and changed (2) flags can be modified by setting $cbflags. The truncated file (4) and narrowed (8) flags are read-only.
\par \pard\plain \s251\sa120\tx2880 \b\f2\fs20\lang1033 \page {\plain \f2\fs16\up6\lang1033 ${\footnote \pard\plain \s245 \f2\fs20\lang1033 {\fs16\up6 $} $cbufname variable}} {\plain \f2\fs16\up6\lang1033 #{\footnote \pard\plain \s245 \f2\fs20\lang1033 {
