 is enabled. If it is FALSE, most messages and prompts are disabled (this is handy to avoid some cases of message line flashing while a macro is running).
\par \pard \s6\sa120 Default value: TRUE.
\par \pard\plain \s251\sa120\tx2880 \b\f2\fs20\lang1033 \page {\plain \f2\fs16\up6\lang1033 ${\footnote \pard\plain \s245 \f2\fs20\lang1033 {\fs16\up6 $} $disinp variable}} {\plain \f2\fs16\up6\lang1033 #{\footnote \pard\plain \s245 \f2\fs20\lang1033 {
