 $exbhook
\par \pard\plain \s6\sa120 \f2\fs20\lang1033 This variable holds the name of a {\ul command}{\v Command} or {\ul macro}{\v Macro} which is run whenever you are switching out of a {\ul buffer}{\v Buffer}.
\par Default value: {\uldb nop}{\v nop}
\par \pard\plain \s251\sa120\tx2880 \b\f2\fs20\lang1033 \page {\plain \f2\fs16\up6\lang1033 ${\footnote \pard\plain \s245 \f2\fs20\lang1033 {\fs16\up6 $} $fcol variable}} {\plain \f2\fs16\up6\lang1033 #{\footnote \pard\plain \s245 \f2\fs20\lang1033 {\fs16\up6 
