\par \pard\plain \s6\sa120 \f2\fs20\lang1033 Within the {\uldb macro language}{\v MacroLanguage}, a semicolon "{\b ;}" signals the beginning of a comment. The text from the semicolon to the end of the line is ignored by MicroEMACS.
\par \pard \s6\sa120 A comment can be the only content of a line, in which case the semicolon must be the first non-blank character on the line. A comment can also appear at the end of any statement.
\par \pard \s6\sa120 Note that empty lines are legal (treated as comments).
